<figureCitation id="10CB2A758617FFCAFACDFA4EC967FA63" captionStart="Figures 7–12" captionStartId="6.[192,288,1725,1747]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,192,1702]" captionTargetId="figure-93@6.[192,1440,192,1702]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 7–12. Six species of Onciderini. Fig. 7. Jamesia duofasciata Dillon and Dillon (a, dorsal habitus; b, labels). Fig. 8. Jamesia fuscofasciata Dillon and Dillon (a, dorsal habitus; b, labels). Fig. 9. Oncideres albifasciata Dillon and Dillon (a, dorsal habitus; b, labels). Fig. 10. Oncideres albistillata Dillon and Dillon (a, dorsal habitus; b, labels). Fig. 11. Oncideres jatai Bondar (a, dorsal habitus; b, labels). Fig. 12. Oncideres ochreomaculata Dillon and Dillon (a, dorsal habitus; b, labels)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5170657" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5170657/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 11a, b</figureCitation>
) is herein designated as the 
<typeStatus id="574B88528617FFCAFDC8FA6ECA88FA63" box="[629,740,1442,1466]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">lectotype</typeStatus>
in order to stabilize the taxonomy and facilitate further identifications of this species.
</paragraph>
